{
  "stem": "15721.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Herman Ezra Schaalman.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's S-C-H-A-A-L-M-A-N.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, except, it was spelled a little differently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Herman had two N's then and Schaalman had two N's.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ezra.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is a Hebrew name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was after a grandfather that had passed away by the time I was born.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "April 28th, 1916.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "80 and a little.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's Munich, Germany.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, basically, of course, Munich was the cultural and so we call it maybe perhaps even intellectual hub of Germany at the time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had lots of artists and theaters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think we had four opera houses that were operating at the same time, one devoted, for instance, entirely to Wagner, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a great university, fine library, one of the great libraries, which incidentally contained one of the very few complete manuscripts of the Babylonian Talmud.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So Munich was a considerable city, as I recall it, both during the times that I lived there and in retrospect.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was about 10,000 Jews living in, in Munich in the '20s after the-- between the two world wars.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a, a, an orthodox community.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the main community was what was known as German liberal, which is closer to what in America would be conservative Judaism.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a very large synagogue that been built in the 1870s, if I remember right.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to the best of my recollection, it seated close to 3,000 people and was really a major edifice down the center of the city, even though it was on a side street.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Incidentally, it was destroyed at the specific instruction of Adolf Hitler because he belonged to a, an artists' club that was right across the street.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he couldn't abide the sight of the synagogue when he looked out the window.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
